text.section:
Unless the articles of merger preclude the right to abandon the merger, a proposed merger may be abandoned before the effective date of the articles by:
Consent of the members of a limited liability company party to the article required to approve the merger under § 4A-702 of this subtitle, or a lesser vote as may be provided for in the operating agreement of the limited liability company;
A majority of the partners of a partnership;
A majority vote of the general partners and a majority in interest of the limited partners, as defined in § 10-208 of this article, of any limited partnership party to the articles;
A majority vote of the entire board of directors of a corporation party to the articles; and
A majority vote of the entire board of trustees of a business trust party to the articles.
